      "section": [
        "Relics",
        "Synopsis"
      ],
      "text": "Team Avatar tours a small Earth Kingdom trading village during their journey to the Northern Water Tribe in search of supplies. While there, Aang meets a merchant who attempts to sell him an authentic Air Nomad pendant. The merchant claims that the necklace is in fact not ancient, and the seller had recently traded it for medicinal supplies. Aang finds out that the necklace comes from caves in the mountains and, while Katara and Sokka are sleeping, sneaks off in order to investigate. When Aang arrives at the cave, he finds many Air Nomad artifacts, but also encounters Admiral Zhao. Zhao's troops quickly capture Aang and show him the merchant who helped lure him into the cave, much like some of the Air Nomad Genocide survivors were lured into the caves and killed by Sozin. However, using the artifacts in the cave, Aang manages to free himself and get back to Katara and Sokka, who have been searching for him since his disappearance."
    },
    {
      "body": "This comic reveals that some ${link_0} did survive the initial attack on the ${link_1} and began to regroup in the Earth Kingdom, but were eventually drawn to caves carved by the ${link_2} that they decorated with Air Nomad artifacts. Using these caves, Sozin sent out rumors saying the Air Nomads could find refuge in these caves, but killed the survivors who went there.",
